2 unit(s) Flatbread
100 g Bocconcini Cheese
113 g Baby Tomatoes
¼ cup Basil Pesto
1 tbsp Italian Seasoning
2 tbsp Balsamic Glaze
113 g Arugula and Spinach Mix
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
28 g Salad Topping Mix
1 unit(s) Green Onion
250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
1 tbsp Oil*
1 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Halve tomatoes.
Thinly slice green onion.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Tear bocconcini into small pieces.
Add bocconcini, garlic, half the Italian Seasoning (use all for 4 ppl) and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then sausage. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min**.

Arrange flatbreads on a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 baking sheets.)
Toast flatbreads in the middle of the oven until lightly crisp, 3-4 min. Remove from oven.
Spread half the pesto over flatbreads, then scatter sausage and bocconcini mixture over top.

Bake flatbreads in the middle of the oven until golden-brown and crisp, 5-7 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, bake flatbreads in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)
Meanwhile, add tomatoes and remaining pesto (use all for 4 ppl) to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine, then set aside.

When flatbreads are almost done, whisk together half the balsamic glaze, 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil in the same large bowl (from step 1).
Add arugula and spinach mix and half the salad topping mix. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Top flatbreads with tomato mixture.
Cut flatbreads into pieces.
Divide salad and flatbreads between plates.
Drizzle remaining balsamic glaze over flatbreads.
Sprinkle green onions overtop.
Sprinkle remaining salad topping mix over salad.

If you've opted to add sausage, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then sausage. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min**.

Top flatbreads with cooked sausage.